N2  - The mean-variance (M-V) rule may lead to paradoxical results which may be resolved by employing the mean coefficient of variation (M-C) rule. It is shown that the M-C rule constitutes an optimal decision rule for lognormal distributions.
AB  - The mean-variance (M-V) rule may lead to paradoxical results which may be resolved by employing the mean coefficient of variation (M-C) rule. It is shown that the M-C rule constitutes an optimal decision rule for lognormal distributions.
